article.description: — Justin Mazzulla had 13 points to lead five Vermont players in double figures as the Catamounts extended their winning streak to 13 games, rolling past Binghamton 82-51 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Mazzulla leads Vermont over Binghamton 82-51
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- — Justin Mazzulla had 13 points to lead five Vermont players in double figures as the Catamounts extended their winning streak to 13 games, rolling past Binghamton 82-51 on Wednesday night. Ben Shungu and Ryan Davis added 11 points apiece, Isaiah Powell and Nick Fiorillo chipped in 10 points each for Vermont (19-4, 11-0 America East Conference). Jacob Falko had 14 points for the Bearcats (10-11, 7-5). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
